
<% priority 10 %>


<% name "Disable Password Auto-complete [1 url]" %>


<b>Description:</b> Password fields that do not have autocomplete turned off allow access to previous password entries on a page. This enables attackers to discover and abuse passwords.<br/>
<b>Affected URLs:</b><br/>

<%= "#{details['login_page']}<br/>" %>


<b>Advice: </b> Turn off the AUTOCOMPLETE attribute in any HTML FORM/INPUT element that is used for passwords.<br/>
